The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a new model that takes into account the Poisson noise statistics, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The model is also optimized for parallel computation on GPUs, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). The authors retrain the model parameters, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and comparisons with state-of-the-art approaches, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
